  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b9f \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A special parliamentary session will be held tomorrow to elect a new president on Wednesday",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Following the vacancy for the presidency, it has been decided in the party leader's meeting to hold a referendum to elect a new president on the 20th of next Wednesday.",
        "Pursuant to Article 4 of the Constitution and the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981, Parliament will meet at 10 a.m. tomorrow.",
        "Section 4 of the Presidential Election (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981 requires Parliament to be convened within three days of the vacancy of the presidency.",
        "According to Article 5, the Parliamentary Secretary shall officially notify the Parliament that the office of the President has become vacant. Speaker Mahinda Yappa Abeywardena has mentioned that the new president will be elected through a referendum on the 20th as previously decided in the party leader's meeting held yesterday.",
        "Accordingly, nomination papers will be requested on the 19th and the election of the new president will be held on the 20th (Tuesday).",
        "The Speaker urged the party leaders that all the members should act in a manner that does not affect the proceedings of the House within the framework of democracy."
      ],
